# {{ project_name }} — Prompt & Agent Guide

## How this works (read once)

The development workflow is **driven by one orchestrator** — the [`autonomous-builder`](../agents/autonomous-builder.agent.md) agent — that reads `roadmap/state.md`, dispatches the subagent that owns the current `Stage`, and loops. You do not run a different prompt for each stage; the orchestrator does.

Prompts (`/`-commands) exist for two reasons:

1. **Manual override**: invoke a stage's owning subagent directly when the orchestrator isn't running, or when you're debugging one step.
2. **Human-only entry points**: actions an autonomous loop can't take on its own — research, vision changes, scrap, catalog activation, the merge handshake.

You almost never type a stage prompt. You select the autonomous-builder, describe your goal, and it drives.

## Primary workflow: select the autonomous-builder

```
VS Code Chat → Agent picker → autonomous-builder → describe your goal
```

Or, for background execution, run it as a Copilot CLI session.

The orchestrator reads `roadmap/state.md`, picks up where it left off, and loops:

```
read Stage → dispatch owning subagent → re-read Stage → advance / loop / stop
```

The subagent for each stage owns that stage's full protocol. The orchestrator does not re-implement any of it.

### First session (greenfield or existing)

On the first run, the orchestrator reads `BOOTSTRAP.md` from the project root:

- **Greenfield**: dispatches the planner subagent for a deep-interview vision draft.
- **Existing project**: dispatches the planner for a codebase-synthesis vision draft.

BOOTSTRAP also asks you to enable `chat.subagents.allowInvocationsFromSubagents` (required for `slice-runner` to dispatch tester/reviewer), pick a `Merge Mode`, and activate any catalog items. Then it cuts a strategy branch and deletes itself.

## Required VS Code settings

| Setting | Value | Why |
|---------|-------|-----|
| `chat.useCustomAgentHooks` | `true` | Enables Stop / PreToolUse / PostToolUse / SubagentStop hooks. Without it, no stage gating, no isolation enforcement, no evidence verification. |
| `chat.subagents.allowInvocationsFromSubagents` | `true` | Required for nesting (orchestrator → slice-runner → tester/reviewer). Without it, every executing slice fails at depth 2. BOOTSTRAP prompts you for this. |
| `chat.autopilot.enabled` (optional) | `true` | Per-tool-call auto-confirmation. Combine with workflow-level `Autopilot: on` in `roadmap/state.md` for fully heads-down sessions. |

## Two layers of autopilot

There are two separate "autopilot" switches; they're independent.

| Switch | Lives in | Controls |
|--------|----------|----------|
| `chat.autopilot.enabled` | VS Code settings | Whether tool calls auto-confirm (no per-call human click). |
| `Autopilot` field in `roadmap/state.md` | Workflow state | Whether the orchestrator pauses at the soft human gates (strategy candidate pick, design approval). |

The merge gate (`awaiting-merge-approval`) **always** pauses regardless of either switch — autopilot cannot do the human's `git push` / `gh pr create`. Vision update, human-decision, and error blocks also always pause.

Flip workflow-level autopilot by editing `roadmap/state.md` once: change `- **Autopilot**: off` to `on`. The line-shape carve-out in `tool-guardrails.py` allows it.

| Mode you want | Copilot autopilot | Workflow autopilot |
|---|---|---|
| Heads-down session, trust the loop | ON | `on` |
| Heads-down execution, but I want to review the design before code | ON | `off` |
| Reviewing each tool call, learning the system | OFF | `off` |

## Agents

### Stage owners (each Stage has exactly one)

| Stage | Owning subagent | What it produces |
|-------|-----------------|------------------|
| `bootstrap` | (BOOTSTRAP.md, no agent) | Vision lock, merge mode, catalog activation, strategy branch |
| `strategy` | [`strategist`](../agents/strategist.agent.md) | Strategy artifact, phase branch, advance to `planning` |
| `planning` | [`planner`](../agents/planner.agent.md) (planning mode) | `roadmap/phases/phase-N-design.md` with Reality Check |
| `design-critique` | [`product-owner`](../agents/product-owner.agent.md) (design mode) → [`critic`](../agents/critic.agent.md) | User stories on the design plan + critique artifact + verdict |
| `implementation-planning` | `planner` (implementation mode) | `roadmap/phases/phase-N-implementation.md` with verified anchors |
| `implementation-critique` | `critic` | Critique artifact + verdict; `record-verdict.py` advances to `executing` |
| `executing` | [`slice-runner`](../agents/slice-runner.agent.md) (once per slice) | Tests + implementation + runtime check + reviewer + commit, per slice |
| `reviewing` | `product-owner` (review mode) | Strategic review artifact; verdict to `pass`/`replan`/`n/a` |
| `cleanup` | [`phase-completer`](../agents/phase-completer.agent.md) | ADRs, doc-sync, wrap summary, merge-gate handoff |
| `blocked` | (no agent — stop) | — |
| `complete` | (no agent — stop) | — |

### Per-slice helpers (invoked by slice-runner, not the orchestrator)

| Agent | Role | When |
|-------|------|------|
| [`tester`](../agents/tester.agent.md) | Writes tests from spec without reading implementation. `tester-isolation.py` enforces. | Step 2 of slice loop |
| [`reviewer`](../agents/reviewer.agent.md) | Per-slice code review + security + doc-sync (warning per slice; merge gate blocks). | Step 7 of slice loop |

### On-demand

| Agent | Role | Invoked by |
|-------|------|-----------|
| [`researcher`](../agents/researcher.agent.md) | Public-source web research producing cited `docs/reference/<topic>.md`. NO terminal access. | `/research <topic>`, or directly when strategist/critic flag an external system without grounding |
| `Explore` (built-in) | Broad read-only searches without polluting main context | Any agent |

### Catalog (activated on demand at bootstrap)

Live in `.github/catalog/agents/`. Copy via `/catalog-review activate <name>`.

| Agent | Role | When to activate |
|-------|------|------------------|
| `designer` | DESIGN.md visual system + browser walkthroughs | Project has frontend/UI; required for the slice loop's runtime check on UI slices |
| `security-reviewer` | OWASP, secrets, auth/authz audit | Project handles auth, payments, or PII |

## Prompts

Prompts are `/` slash-commands you type in chat. They split into three groups.

### Group 1 — Manual overrides for stages the orchestrator drives

You almost never run these. They exist so a human can drive a single stage manually if needed (debugging, recovery from interrupted run).

| Prompt | Stage | Dispatches |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| `/strategize` | `strategy` | `strategist` |
| `/design-plan` | `planning` | `planner` (planning mode) |
| `/implementation-plan` | `implementation-planning` | `planner` (implementation mode) |
| `/implement` | `executing` | `slice-runner` (one slice) |
| `/code-review` | (per slice) | `reviewer` |
| `/strategic-review` | `reviewing` | `product-owner` (review mode) |
| `/phase-complete` | `cleanup` | `phase-completer` |

### Group 2 — Human-only entry points

These are the prompts you actually type.

| Prompt | When to type it |
|--------|-----------------|
| `/resume` | After any session that ended with `Stage: blocked`. Routes by `Blocked Kind`. |
| `/merge-phase` | At the merge gate (`awaiting-merge-approval`). Prints the merge commands or PR URL; the human runs them. |
| `/research <topic>` | You want a durable reference doc on something external. |
| `/vision-expand` | The current vision is exhausted (`vision-exhausted` block). |
| `/scrap-phase` | You want to abandon the current phase entirely. |
| `/catalog-review` | You want to activate (or audit) catalog items. |

### Group 3 — `/code-review` and `/research` are dual-purpose

`/research` is also dispatched by strategist/critic when external grounding is needed. `/code-review` is also dispatched by slice-runner. You can also invoke them directly.

## State writers (sanctioned helpers)

Direct edits to `roadmap/state.md` are restricted by `tool-guardrails.py` (the threat model is forging `Stage: bootstrap` to unlock the enforcement-layer carve-out). Helpers exist for fields with cross-field invariants or validation logic:

| Helper | Fields written | Why a helper |
|---|---|---|
| `write-stage.py` | `Stage`, `Blocked Kind`, `Blocked Reason`, `Next Prompt` | Bootstrap-forging gate + enforces `Stage=blocked ⇒ Blocked Kind` invariant |
| `write-phase.py` | `Phase`, `Phase Title`, optional 17-field evidence reset | Phase boundary resets are too error-prone by hand |
| `write-plan-evidence.py` | `Design/Implementation Plan`, `Design/Implementation Status`, `Slice Total` | Validates plan-file existence + status vocabulary |
| `write-test-evidence.py` | `Tests Written`, `Tests Pass`, `Evidence For Slice` | Auto-binds `Evidence For Slice` to current `Active Slice` |
| `write-commit-evidence.py` | `Committed` | Refuses to stamp `yes` if working tree is dirty |
| `record-verdict.py` | Critique-verdict mutations: `Design/Implementation Status`, `Critique Rounds`, plus `Stage`/`Blocked Kind`/`Next Prompt`. Honors `Autopilot` for design-approve. | Enforces round budget + `^VERDICT:` trailer requirement |
| `cut-branch.py` | (git only — no state.md write) | Centralises strategy/phase branch cuts; refuses dirty tree; idempotent |

For everything else (`Active Slice`, `Reviewer Invoked`, `Review Verdict`, `Critical Findings`, `Major Findings`, `Strategic Review`, `Merge Mode`, `Autopilot`), edit the line directly via `replace_string_in_file`. The line-shape carve-out validates the edit is exactly one `- **Field**: value` change.

## Hooks (lifecycle enforcement)

| Hook | Event | What it does |
|------|-------|--------------|
| `stage-gate.py` | PreToolUse | Blocks edits outside `roadmap/`, `docs/`, `.github/` during non-executing stages. Fails closed on unknown Stage. |
| `tool-guardrails.py` | PreToolUse | Denies destructive commands (force-push, rm -rf on critical paths, curl|sh, etc.) and writes to enforcement-layer paths. |
| `branch-gate.py` | PreToolUse | Refuses `git commit` on `main`/`master`/`trunk`/`prod`. Bootstrap exempt. |
| `tester-isolation.py` | PreToolUse (tester only) | Denies `semantic_search`/`codebase` entirely; path-gates reads to test+config patterns. |
| `evidence-tracker.py` | PostToolUse | Logs tool-call summaries to `roadmap/sessions/<sessionId>.md`. Pure logger. |
| `context-pressure.py` | PostToolUse | Advisory at high context usage. |
| `subagent-verdict-check.py` | SubagentStop | Verifies critic/product-owner/reviewer/planner wrote their state fields and produced their artifact. |
| `session-gate.py` | Stop | Refuses stop on incomplete Slice Evidence (during `executing`); refuses stop on `Stage: blocked` + `Blocked Kind: n/a`; surfaces `Next Prompt` on every stop. |

## How prompts & agents work (mechanics)

- **Prompt files** (`.prompt.md`) — invoked via `/` in Chat. Per the [VS Code docs](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot/customization/prompt-files): "you invoke prompt files manually in chat." They cannot be invoked from inside another agent's reasoning loop. The orchestrator drives stages by dispatching **subagents**, not by calling prompts.
- **Custom agents** (`.agent.md`) — selected in the agent picker (or invoked as subagents by other agents). Have their own tool restrictions, hooks, handoffs.
- **Subagents** — agent-callable workers with isolated context. Per the VS Code docs: "the main agent recognizes the part of the task that benefits from isolated context. The agent starts a subagent, passing only the relevant subtask. The subagent works autonomously and returns a summary." This is the primitive the orchestrator uses for every stage.
- **Instruction files** (`.instructions.md`) — applied automatically when files match `applyTo` glob.
- **Hooks** — deterministic shell commands at agent lifecycle points. JSON in/out per [hooks docs](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot/customization/hooks).
- **Skills** (`.github/skills/`) — multi-file capabilities. Created by phase-completer for stack technologies.
- **Workflow catalog** (`.github/catalog/`) — dormant capabilities activated at bootstrap. Index in `MANIFEST.md`.

Markdown links in prompt/agent bodies auto-attach referenced files as context. Use that to keep agent files lean.

## Branch hygiene — handled by `cut-branch.py`

You don't manually run `git checkout -b` for workflow branches. The helper covers the four transitions:

| Transition | Helper invocation | Where it's called |
|---|---|---|
| End of bootstrap | `cut-branch.py strategy` | BOOTSTRAP.md Step 6 |
| Strategy approval (inline pick) | `cut-branch.py phase --number N --title "..."` | strategist subagent |
| `/resume awaiting-strategy-approval` pick | same | resume prompt |
| `/resume awaiting-merge-approval` (post-merge) | `cut-branch.py strategy --pull` | resume prompt |

The helper refuses to run on a dirty tree, switches off any old `phase/*` branch to trunk before cutting (avoids carrying scrapped commits forward), and is idempotent (re-runs check out the existing branch).

## Troubleshooting

- **Slice-runner immediately fails** — check `chat.subagents.allowInvocationsFromSubagents` is `true`. Default is `false`; nesting is required for slice-runner to dispatch tester/reviewer.
- **Branch-gate denies a commit** — you're on `main`/`master`/`trunk`/`prod`. The orchestrator should never have committed here outside bootstrap. Re-dispatch the subagent that should have cut the branch (strategist for phase, resume for strategy).
- **Stop hook blocks session end** — read its message. Usually: incomplete Slice Evidence (finish the slice), or `Stage: blocked` + `Blocked Kind: n/a` (set the kind via `write-stage.py`).
- **Prompt doesn't appear in `/` menu** — check it's in `.github/prompts/` with `.prompt.md` extension, and `Chat: Reload Window` if you just added it.
- **Agent can't find files** — don't add a `tools` field unless restricting; default agent has full access.
- **Subagent returned without updating state** — `subagent-verdict-check.py` should have blocked it; check `chat.useCustomAgentHooks: true`.
- **Diagnostics**: Right-click in Chat view → Diagnostics to see all loaded prompts/agents/skills and any errors.
